Important engineering rules:

* Keep the architecture modular.
* Do not hardcode Cursor internals.
* Make it work in VS Code first, so it also works in Cursor.
* Use strict TypeScript.
* Avoid overengineering.
* Make task routing easy to debug.
* Log every routing decision.
* Every task should have a human-readable reason for why it was created or appended.
* Do not allow two running workers to modify the same locked file.
* Prefer queueing over unsafe parallel edits.
* The UI should be simple but clear.
